# Due to mapping, shared_region.narrowPeak, human_specific.narrowPeak and mouse_specific.narrowPeak, mouse_to_human
# The original narrowPeak cols:
1  chrom
2  start
3  end
4  name
5  score (0–1000)
6  strand
7  signalValue
8  pValue (-log10)
9  qValue (-log10)
10 peak (summit offset)

# Due to mapping, shared_region.narrowPeak, human_specific.narrowPeak and mouse_specific.narrowPeak, mouse_to_human.narrowPeak
# the values in 5-9 is meaningless, may need to attach to raw narrowPeak for partten analysis
# as if you want to do MEME(pattern analysis) in "Find sequence patterns that occur more than expected by chance in each of the following
